---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <div class="pt-16 md:pt-24 pb-16 px-4 md:px-16">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">
        Code of Conduct
      </h1>

      <p class="text-lg md:text-xl font-sans text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-12 max-w-prose">
        At Thinkin' Rocks, we believe innovation happens best in an environment of respect, safety, and fairness. All community sessions and hardware use follow this Code of Conduct. By joining, you agree to these rules.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-10 max-w-prose">
        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-mono text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Behaviour We Don't Tolerate
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 font-sans text-base md:text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <li>Verbal or written disrespect towards any participant or organiser</li>
            <li>Intimidation, harassment, or threats of any kind</li>
            <li>Inappropriate physical contact</li>
            <li>Sustained disruption of events, sessions, or workspace</li>
            <li>Unsafe use of equipment or ignoring safety instructions</li>
            <li>Encouraging or advocating any of the above</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-mono text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Hardware Use & Intellectual Property
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 font-sans text-base md:text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Reservation required:</span> All tools and hardware must be booked in advance through our system. Please respect time slots so everyone has fair access.
            </p>
            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Care & responsibility:</span> Treat all shared equipment as if it were your own. Misuse or damage through negligence may result in suspension of access.
            </p>
            <p>
              <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900">Your IP is yours:</span> Anything you build, code, or design at Thinkin' Rocks belongs to you (and your collaborators, if agreed). Thinkin' Rocks does not claim ownership of members' work.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-mono text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Repercussions of Violations
          </h2>
          <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 font-sans text-base md:text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <li>Unacceptable behaviour will not be tolerated. Anyone asked to stop must comply immediately.</li>
            <li>Organisers may take action they deem appropriate: warning, suspension, or expulsion from sessions and the community.</li>
            <li>Repeated or severe violations may result in a permanent ban.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-mono text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Reporting Violations
          </h2>
          <p class="font-sans text-base md:text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            If you are subjected to unacceptable behaviour, notice someone else being subjected to it, or have any concerns, please notify a Thinkin' Rocks organiser or contact the designated persons below as soon as possible. All reports will be handled confidentially and thoroughly. In urgent or severe cases, third parties such as university safety staff or the police may be involved.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section>
          <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-mono text-gray-900 mb-4">
            Harassment Contact Persons
          </h2>
          <div class="space-y-4 font-sans text-base md:text-lg text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
            <p>
              <span class="font-medium text-gray-900">Milana Begantsova</span> (she/her)<br>
              <a href="mailto:milana@thinkinrocks.com?subject=Code%20of%20Conduct%20Report&body=Hi%20Milana,%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20need%20to%20report%20a%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20violation%20at%20Thinkin'%20Rocks.%0D%0A%0D%0ADate%20and%20time:%20%0D%0ALocation:%20%0D%0APeople%20involved:%20%0D%0A%0D%0ADescription%20of%20what%20happened:%0D%0A%0D%0A%0D%0AAdditional%20information:%0D%0A%0D%0A%0D%0AThank%20you%20for%20your%20time." class="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-800 transition-colors">milana@thinkinrocks.com</a>
            </p>
            <p>
              <span class="font-medium text-gray-900">Yerzhan Zhamashev</span> (he/his)<br>
              <a href="mailto:yerzhan@thinkinrocks.com?subject=Code%20of%20Conduct%20Report&body=Hi%20Yerzhan,%0D%0A%0D%0AI%20need%20to%20report%20a%20Code%20of%20Conduct%20violation%20at%20Thinkin'%20Rocks.%0D%0A%0D%0ADate%20and%20time:%20%0D%0ALocation:%20%0D%0APeople%20involved:%20%0D%0A%0D%0ADescription%20of%20what%20happened:%0D%0A%0D%0A%0D%0AAdditional%20information:%0D%0A%0D%0A%0D%0AThank%20you%20for%20your%20time." class="text-purple-600 hover:text-purple-800 transition-colors">yerzhan@thinkinrocks.com</a>
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
